# Neoma requires no environment variables to run.
#
# Neoma is local-first and makes no external API calls, so there are no
# secrets, API keys, or service URLs to configure to USE the app. This file
# documents optional build-time variables. Copy it to `.env` (git-ignored) and
# fill in only what you need.

# Port used by `npm run dev` (Vite). Defaults to 5173.
# VITE_PORT=5173

# ===========================================================================
# Apple signing — ONLY for signing/notarising the macOS app and building the
# iOS app. Not needed for the browser/PWA build or an unsigned local build.
#
# Cargo/Tauri do not auto-load .env. Before a signed build, load it first:
#     set -a; source .env; set +a
#     npm run desktop:build
#
# Easiest local path: open src-tauri/gen/apple/Neoma.xcodeproj in Xcode and use
# automatic signing (pick your team) — then you only need the team IDs below.
# Reference: https://tauri.app/distribute/sign/macos/ and /distribute/sign/ios/
# ===========================================================================

# --- Identity (NOT secret) ---
# Your 10-character Apple Developer Team ID (Apple Developer -> Membership).
# APPLE_TEAM_ID=XXXXXXXXXX
# Signing identity exactly as shown in Keychain Access, e.g.
#   "Developer ID Application: Your Name (XXXXXXXXXX)"  (direct .dmg), or
#   "Apple Development"                                  (local test builds).
# APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY=

# --- Notarisation (so a downloaded .dmg opens without a Gatekeeper warning) ---
# Apple ID email + an APP-SPECIFIC password (appleid.apple.com). SECRET.
# APPLE_ID=
# APPLE_PASSWORD=

# --- iOS (usually the same value as APPLE_TEAM_ID) ---
# TAURI_APPLE_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM=XXXXXXXXXX

# --- CI only (headless, no Keychain). SECRET. Leave blank locally. ---
#   base64 -i certificate.p12 | pbcopy
# APPLE_CERTIFICATE=
# APPLE_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD=
